<headline>Heat Advisory issued July 22 at 3:06AM CDT until July 24 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Saint Louis</headline>
<description>...HEAT ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 8 PM CDT SUNDAY...
* WHAT...Heat index values up to 109 expected.
* WHERE...Portions of south central and southwest Illinois. Portions
of central, east central, northeast, and southeast Missouri.
* WHEN...From Noon today to 8 PM CDT Sunday.
* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.</description>
<instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.
People in the Saint Louis Metropolitan Area can get information
about cooling centers or energy assistance related to the excessive
heat by calling the United Way of Greater Saint Louis at
800-427-4626, or if calling from a land line phone dial 2-1-1. You
can also call Cool Down Saint Louis at 314-241-7668.</instruction>
